            <h3>You</h3>
            <p>We honestly don't care who or what you are, because frankly that's none of our business. 
               We don't require any information from you aside from an e-mail address which we may 
               contact you on. Any information you provide to us will remain with us and not be sent 
               offshore to a spam mining company.</p>

            <h3>Data</h3>
            <p>We promise we're not going to release any data to anyone you don't want it released to, 
               except the authorities. But only if they're requesting specific items with a warrant 
               and all that legal shit. Also, we'll fight tooth and nail for you because that big 
               brother shit sucks.</p>
            <p>The only ones that can view your data are the operators of cloudlab.io. We've got 
               controls in place to only view your data if the situation warrants it (such as support 
               requests that you initiate) and only if there's a real need to. Honestly, we just don't
               give a rats ass about your SUPER SECRET PROJECT. We've got enough trouble working on 
               our own here with cloudlab!   
            <p>Also, we're not HIPAA- or PCI- or whatever compliant (yet), so don't think that this 
               is the best place for <em>that</em> kind of data. We'll modify this section if/when
               this situation changes.</p>

            <h3>Tracking & Analytics</h3>
            <p>We use Google Analytics to see what we're doing right and what's going wrong or not 
               being utilized. We don't release this data to anyone, although technically Google 
               probably could. Anyway, we only use this data for quality assurance and to make the 
               service better. That's it.</p>
            <p>The best we can tell is what city you come from and what kind of language/browser 
               you're using, not other stuff like you're a my little pony fan or that you have a 
               problem with your &hellip; never mind.</p>
